# Project plan (HTML) — design system

When you edit the **Combined Gantt**, **Outcome Maps**, or **Kanban** HTML, follow the full spec in [Documentation/Project-Plan-Design-System.md](../../Documentation/Project-Plan-Design-System.md) for: three layers, file layout, **brand and colors**, layer-specific UI (tabs, grid, **+** links, dependency SVG, hash routing, columns, tooltips), and **WBS** as the source of outcome/deliverable data.

## Non-negotiables

- **No** external CDNs, npm, or frameworks. Vanilla inline HTML/CSS/JS only. **No build.** **Relative** links (no leading `/`). **No** `localStorage` / `sessionStorage` for kanban. **No FTE** in Combined Gantt summary cards or bar labels.

Capability-specific stable IDs, outcome conventions, and WBS section structure: [`.cursor/rules/pa.mdc`](pa.mdc), [`vi.mdc`](vi.mdc), [`wm.mdc`](wm.mdc), [`wb.mdc`](wb.mdc) and the relevant `*-WBS.md` files.
